BODHAM. Letter of Anthony, bp. of Norwich, appropriating the church of Bodham to the
              abbot and convent of Langley. Dated at Norwich, 1330 ;
              confirmed by the prior and convent of Norwich, 27 August, same year. MS. Ch. Norfolk 231.

STOKE. Receipt given by Nicholas, the abbot of Langley, to Bartholomew White, esq.,
              for the payment of 35. 4^. for a farm in Stoke. Dated Monday after Palm Sunday,
                 18 Ed. IV. MS. Ch. Norfolk 234.

Account of Peter de Broke, servant of the sacrist of the church of Norwich, for the
              said manor, i5th year of H. Prior, i.e. 1304-5. [i membrane
              ] MS. Rolls Norfolk 22.
